  "body": "# Bug Report\r\n\r\n\r\n## Problem \r\n\r\nIf Keycard was frozen in logged-in state, e.g. when signing a transaction or changing some passcode, and User taps `Dismiss` in the pop-up and navigate to `Change PIN` (PUK / pairing) screen, the `Reset passcode with PUK` starts, even if the PUK has not been set previously.\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n\r\n`Keycard is frozen` pop-up when opening any screen when the passcode is required\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n\r\n\r\nhttps://user-images.githubusercontent.com/67952253/126484847-2eca72ec-9090-4dbe-ae1e-6fa293ecf18d.mp4\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n1. Recover Keycard account\r\n2. Settings > Keycard > Change 6-digit passcode\r\n3. Enter invalid passcode 3 times (or freeze Keycard in any other way being logged-in)\r\n4. Tap `Dismiss` in the pop-up\r\n5. Tap back\r\n6. Open `Change 12-digit PUK`\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n- Status version: nightly 21/07\r\n- Operating System: Android, iOS\r\n\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Please, add logs/notes if necessary)\r\n\r\n",
