    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I think we should re-think a bit this interaction, because now that we have backup cards, we probably shouldn't block any flow, because we don't know what card will be tapped after selecting an action.\r\n\r\nmy proposal is:\r\n\r\n1. all menu, options etc assume you have a working/not blocked keycard so when you open them you get the intended functionality\r\n2. if the tapped card is blocked, the pop-up is displayed as a reaction to this (this happens already)\r\n3. we stop storing the \"frozen\" state completely and thus remove the corresponding banner from the wallet page\r\n\r\nnot completely sure about the last point since it is a nice and visible entry point to the reset flow, however since any flow will display the popup (including login) I don't know if it make sense to have a \"frozen\" state.\r\n\r\nso long story short I would propose fixing this bug by having the change pin/puk/pairing always display the intended screen and only show the popup if a blocked card is tapped when verifying the PIN. Optionally, completely remove the frozen state.\r\n\r\nwdyt?\r\n\r\n/cc @guylouis ",
